      {
        "id": "e7eda0a67363edcf7b19e27f2e8dd946dc78037c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7680,
          "name": "Renu Kumari",
          "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
          "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
          "username": "renukumari"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2022-03-24 16:27:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI noticed that we define pluginManagement in cps-parent instead of cps-bom and cps-dependencies. \n\nThe spotbugs and checkstyle don't extend from cps-parent but I am wondering if they never needed this plugin before then why to add pluginManagement here.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "1d981f23dc1848a49513832445c1cdf9d034be3d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7931,
          "name": "Lee Anjella Macabuhay",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "lee.anjella.macabuhay@est.tech",
          "username": "emaclee"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2022-03-25 09:44:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> \n> I noticed that we define pluginManagement in cps-parent instead of cps-bom and cps-dependencies. \n> \n> The spotbugs and checkstyle don't extend from cps-parent but I am wondering if they never needed this plugin before then why to add pluginManagement here.\n\nhi renu.  without specifying the plugin version for this module, it by default pulls version 2.8.1 that is why we need to add it here so it uses 2.8.2 - using 2.8.1 actually ignores the data from the settings.xml that they are passing",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "e9a8ad94dc2db59c88fa68117f1d53351ede39da",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7931,
          "name": "Lee Anjella Macabuhay",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "lee.anjella.macabuhay@est.tech",
          "username": "emaclee"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2022-03-25 11:43:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> > \n> > I noticed that we define pluginManagement in cps-parent instead of cps-bom and cps-dependencies. \n> > \n> > The spotbugs and checkstyle don't extend from cps-parent but I am wondering if they never needed this plugin before then why to add pluginManagement here.\n> \n> hi renu.  without specifying the plugin version for this module, it by default pulls version 2.8.1 that is why we need to add it here so it uses 2.8.2 - using 2.8.1 actually ignores the data from the settings.xml that they are passing\n\n**using 2.7 instead of 2.8",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "0ab431e3247908b66070a9bba241872fa9a2edd2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7680,
          "name": "Renu Kumari",
          "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
          "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
          "username": "renukumari"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2022-03-25 12:59:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > > Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> > > \n> > > I noticed that we define pluginManagement in cps-parent instead of cps-bom and cps-dependencies. \n> > > \n> > > The spotbugs and checkstyle don't extend from cps-parent but I am wondering if they never needed this plugin before then why to add pluginManagement here.\n> > \n> > hi renu.  without specifying the plugin version for this module, it by default pulls version 2.8.1 that is why we need to add it here so it uses 2.8.2 - using 2.8.1 actually ignores the data from the settings.xml that they are passing\n> \n> **using 2.7 instead of 2.8\n\nThanks Lee Angella, I understand the reason. Because we are pushing maven artifacts of dependencies, bom, checkstyle, and spotbugs, we had to add these to all the projects which are not extending from cps-parent. And cps-parent imports cps-bom  & dependencies therefore it automatically gets the suggested plugin version and no need to add explicitly in cps-parent.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
